    "body": "Thanks for raising this @hukkinj1.\r\n\r\nIt seems the issue is here:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/9ed65a64f8fc518c98b381e628556df9bf906acb/validator_client/src/config.rs#L109-L111\r\n\r\nWe assume that if `beacon-nodes` is `Some`, then it has been provided on the CLI. However, this is not true since it has a default value and will always be `Some`:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/sigp/lighthouse/blob/9ed65a64f8fc518c98b381e628556df9bf906acb/validator_client/src/cli.rs#L26\r\n\r\nI think we need to use [`is_present`](https://docs.rs/clap/3.0.0-beta.2/clap/struct.ArgMatches.html#method.is_present) instead. I'm not certain, but *I think* it allows us to differentiate between the default value and no provided value. Unit testing would be required to prove this.\r\n\r\nThis is indeed a bug, and an annoying one at that. I reviewed the PR that contained this bug and I failed to catch it. My sincere apologies.",
